Type |Switching Type | Reserved |I| +-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+ LSP Encoding Type (8 bits): see [RFC3471] for a description of parameters. Switching Type (8 bits): see [RFC3471] for a description of parameters. I flag (1 bit): the I flag indicates whether a layer with the specified switching type and encoding type must or must not be used by the computed path. When the I flag is set (one), the computed path MUST traverse a layer with the specified switching type and encoding type. When the I flag is clear (zero), the computed path
